The paper deals with signal processing techniques to extract individual packets from collided signals in random-access networks, which is a common problem in wireless communication systems. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a decoding scheme that incorporates symbol misalignment into the channel decoding process, which involves machine learning and signal processing techniques, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Signal Processing (cs.SI), or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
